Condition : 3 - No development shall take place until full details and samples of all materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development hereby permitted have been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. Details must include a detailed schedule of materials, a photographic sample board and rendered drawings, elevations and sections at a sufficient scale (1:20 or 1:50) to illustrate how all external materials will appear together.
The samples and details shall include: 
(a)	Samples of brickwork (including brick, masonry, brick panels, feature brick panel, brick framing feature and mortar on-site sample panel, minimum one metre by one metre) including all mortar colours, joint type and brick bond, to achieve closest match to existing as possible;
(b)	Samples of cladding materials (including specifications where relevant);
(c)	Any roof coverings, including parapet coping / capping materials, dormers and canopies;
(d)	Window types; and sectional drawings of reveals / sills / head details 
(e)	Balustrading treatment and handrails to balconies and roof areas (including details / sections / materials); and
(f)	Any other materials/details / fittings to be used (including solar panels, extract vents, rainwater goods, boiler flues etc.), with sections and on-site samples where appropriate.
Details shall also have been submitted and approved in writing by the local planning authority in respect of landscaping features, including furniture, planting plans and surfacing materials, for the staff roof terrace, and any other matters such as site lighting or other surfacing / planting alterations to the rest of the site.
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details and maintained as such thereafter.

Condition : 4 - Prior to commencement of any above ground works, full details of the proposed green roofs shall have been submitted to the Local Planning Authority for approval in writing, including planting schedules and maintenance and management arrangements. Details shall include: 
(i)	Construction drawings, including a detailed plan and cross sections; 
(ii)	Specifications of a native wildflower seed mix (turf or sedum blanket will not be accepted), together with use of small piles of untreated logs; 
(iii)	Evidence that a substrate of between 80mm-150mm in depth will be achieved, which shall be undulating and contain different materials/ sizes (sand, gravel, crushed ceramic, brick, recycled, inert materials); 
(iv)	Confirmation that no irrigation will be used; 
(v)	Confirmation that the green roof construction will be supervised by a suitable qualified landscape/ecology contractor; and 
(vi)      Details of a scheme for ongoing periodic maintenance and management of the green roof.
The approved details shall be implemented and retained permanently thereafter.

